bowser
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number: 2
Definition:a dispenser attached to inverted spirit-bottle in a hotel bar which automatically measures and dispenses a fluid ounce or `nip'.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ?1950s A recent commentator [on the six o'clock swill] suggested, only just satirically, that the logical development of the present bar would be `a huge beer bowser with numerous coin-in-the-slot nipples on the end of plastic hoses.
